2
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:31,830
(Episode 3)

3
00:02:27,079 --> 00:02:28,079
Sorry

4
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:30,320
for disturbing you.

5
00:02:33,110 --> 00:02:34,110
No.

6
00:02:34,430 --> 00:02:36,350
My hearing is too good.

7
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:40,750
I couldn't save that girl.

8
00:02:41,510 --> 00:02:42,940
What a shame.

9
00:02:44,590 --> 00:02:45,750
You look sad.

10
00:02:46,270 --> 00:02:48,470
It's not just about Wang Xiaoyi, right?

11
00:02:51,550 --> 00:02:52,550
That's right.

12
00:02:52,829 --> 00:02:56,030
I didn't save my daughter either.

13
00:02:57,230 --> 00:02:58,740
If she were still alive,

14
00:03:01,150 --> 00:03:02,870
she should be about your age.

15
00:03:04,230 --> 00:03:05,230
I'm sorry.

16
00:03:06,950 --> 00:03:07,990
How did she...

17
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:09,680
Wolf plague.

18
00:03:11,630 --> 00:03:12,630
Back then...

19
00:03:16,390 --> 00:03:17,390
Look.

20
00:03:17,990 --> 00:03:20,470
The snow is beautiful tonight.

21
00:03:23,030 --> 00:03:25,950
My daughter loved snow the most.

22
00:03:28,230 --> 00:03:29,230
Yeah.

23
00:03:29,550 --> 00:03:30,950
The snow is so beautiful.

24
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:41,270
The snow brought you to tears?

25
00:03:42,150 --> 00:03:43,430
How rare.

26
00:03:52,230 --> 00:03:54,950
It's no good to lean on the railing alone.

27
00:03:55,430 --> 00:03:56,430
Very unsafe.

28
00:03:58,430 --> 00:04:00,230
By the way, Madame,

29
00:04:00,870 --> 00:04:02,680
this is my good friend.

30
00:04:02,790 --> 00:04:03,850
He has a kind heart.

31
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:07,170
I fear that he'll run into some
villainous hypocrites.

32
00:04:08,230 --> 00:04:09,910
Please watch him for me.

33
00:04:09,990 --> 00:04:11,450
Don't let others harm him.

34
00:04:13,830 --> 00:04:14,830
Of course.

35
00:04:15,830 --> 00:04:18,230
Well, you guys have a good chat.

36
00:04:19,829 --> 00:04:20,829
I have to go.

37
00:04:59,790 --> 00:05:00,990
It's soaked in blood.

38
00:05:01,190 --> 00:05:02,190
Who cares?

39
00:05:02,710 --> 00:05:04,270
Shall we move it to the patriarch?

40
00:05:04,270 --> 00:05:06,130
Let's try and see if we can move it.

41
00:05:06,630 --> 00:05:07,630
Come on.

42
00:05:10,390 --> 00:05:11,390
It's so light.

43
00:05:12,990 --> 00:05:15,120
It's even more wicked than that thing.

44
00:05:16,340 --> 00:05:18,190
Let's send it to the patriarch.

45
00:05:19,030 --> 00:05:20,030
Come on,

46
00:05:20,180 --> 00:05:21,390
are you serious now?

47
00:05:22,270 --> 00:05:23,930
Are you really moving it away?

48
00:05:24,550 --> 00:05:25,830
The carpenter said,

49
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:27,230
the key is in the coffin.

50
00:05:27,590 --> 00:05:29,590
Just open the coffin and get the key.

51
00:05:32,430 --> 00:05:33,690
It's not a trap, right?

52
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:38,110
Give me a hand.

53
00:05:41,110 --> 00:05:42,230
The coffin is so light,

54
00:05:42,230 --> 00:05:43,490
but the lid is so heavy.

55
00:06:10,150 --> 00:06:11,150
Take it.

56
00:06:14,590 --> 00:06:15,590
Is this the key?

57
00:06:15,950 --> 00:06:16,950
Looks normal.

58
00:06:17,150 --> 00:06:18,150
What?

59
00:06:18,270 --> 00:06:20,130
Do you need background music too?

60
00:06:20,510 --> 00:06:22,110
Ruan Baijie is so kind to you.

61
00:06:22,630 --> 00:06:24,360
Usually, the one who get the key

62
00:06:24,510 --> 00:06:26,310
will be the first to open the door

63
00:06:27,030 --> 00:06:29,090
and get a direct clue of the next door.

64
00:06:29,550 --> 00:06:31,430
It's like you're halfway to the next door.

65
00:06:31,430 --> 00:06:33,230
Alright, everyone is happy now.

66
00:06:33,390 --> 00:06:34,550
I'll be kind again

67
00:06:34,670 --> 00:06:36,680
and tell you where the door is.

68
00:06:37,110 --> 00:06:38,170
You found the door?

69
00:06:38,190 --> 00:06:39,030
Of course.

70
00:06:39,030 --> 00:06:40,030
Where is it?

71
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:40,950
In the well.

72
00:06:40,950 --> 00:06:41,950
In the well?

73
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:43,570
Are you kidding me?

74
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:45,470
The monster is still in the well.

75
00:06:46,150 --> 00:06:48,240
It's not your first time crossing the door.

76
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:49,430
Don't you know that

77
00:06:49,670 --> 00:06:50,909
the door is most likely to be

78
00:06:50,909 --> 00:06:52,630
where monsters exist?

79
00:06:52,830 --> 00:06:54,120
The monster is in the well.

80
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:55,230
How can we find the door?

81
00:06:55,230 --> 00:06:56,230
Easy.

82
00:06:56,230 --> 00:06:57,430
Feed her a dead thing.

83
00:06:57,590 --> 00:06:58,630
When she's full,

84
00:06:58,830 --> 00:07:00,430
we will get through the door.

85
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:04,150
What dead things do we have here to feed her?

86
00:07:04,750 --> 00:07:06,750
You don't. But I do.

87
00:07:20,030 --> 00:07:21,310
Take a break.

88
00:07:25,620 --> 00:07:27,480
Can we see the door when we go down?

89
00:07:32,230 --> 00:07:33,830
I have to tell you something.

90
00:07:36,230 --> 00:07:37,690
Aren't you gonna do it now?

91
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,370
The door will open soon.

92
00:07:39,390 --> 00:07:40,740
Why are you waiting for?

93
00:07:40,790 --> 00:07:42,920
If you don't do it, when the door opens,

94
00:07:43,030 --> 00:07:44,950
the clue will fall into Ling Jiushi's hands.

95
00:07:44,950 --> 00:07:46,810
What should we tell the boss then?

96
00:07:48,190 --> 00:07:49,390
I just think that

97
00:07:50,870 --> 00:07:52,590
we shouldn't fight with Ling Jiushi.

98
00:07:52,590 --> 00:07:54,310
There is no should or shouldn't.

99
00:07:54,310 --> 00:07:55,680
If we fail to finish our task,

100
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,590
we will be miserable when we get back.

101
00:07:57,590 --> 00:07:58,720
Let's play it by ear.

102
00:07:59,150 --> 00:08:01,010
Why are you acting so mysterious?

103
00:08:01,470 --> 00:08:02,470
Well,

104
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:04,390
I still think this is too precious.

105
00:08:04,390 --> 00:08:05,790
I want to return it to you.

106
00:08:06,190 --> 00:08:07,190
I gave it to you.

107
00:08:08,030 --> 00:08:09,030
It's yours.

108
00:08:14,630 --> 00:08:15,630
Anything else?

109
00:08:17,830 --> 00:08:20,480
Is Ruan Baijie your alias?

110
00:08:20,790 --> 00:08:21,790
Of course.

111
00:08:23,550 --> 00:08:25,150
You want to know my real name?

112
00:08:25,710 --> 00:08:28,170
What's wrong? Are you reluctant to leave me?

113
00:08:28,550 --> 00:08:30,430
No, I don't mean anything else.

114
00:08:30,430 --> 00:08:32,090
I just want to return it to you.

115
00:08:39,350 --> 00:08:40,350
Let's go.

116
00:08:41,070 --> 00:08:42,200
They are rushing us.

117
00:08:55,870 --> 00:08:58,510
Can we go down now?

118
00:08:59,030 --> 00:09:00,030
Yes.

119
00:09:31,230 --> 00:09:32,230
Don't move.

120
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:34,750
Let's go.

121
00:10:18,870 --> 00:10:20,070
Hurry! Open the door!

122
00:10:31,830 --> 00:10:33,030
Goodbye, my friends.

123
00:10:34,830 --> 00:10:36,090
Stop being emotional.

124
00:10:41,270 --> 00:10:42,270
Let me help you.

125
00:10:51,470 --> 00:10:52,470
Keep up!

126
00:11:29,430 --> 00:11:30,550
It's all your fault.

127
00:11:30,550 --> 00:11:31,830
You were dilly-dallying.

128
00:11:31,830 --> 00:11:33,030
The key shouldn't be given to you.

129
00:11:33,030 --> 00:11:34,230
What should we do now?

130
00:11:34,790 --> 00:11:35,850
In that situation,

131
00:11:35,950 --> 00:11:37,080
can you keep it safe?

132
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:39,390
Right, it's all my fault.

133
00:11:40,470 --> 00:11:41,600
I will think of a way.

134
00:11:47,230 --> 00:11:48,630
There's wind in the cave.

135
00:11:49,630 --> 00:11:50,750
This cave is an arc,

136
00:11:50,870 --> 00:11:51,930
so there's a swirl.

137
00:11:52,030 --> 00:11:53,500
If we can eliminate interference,

138
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:54,590
we'll find the way.

139
00:11:56,190 --> 00:11:57,920
Where did you get this lighter?

140
00:11:58,110 --> 00:11:59,110
Why do you care?

141
00:11:59,350 --> 00:12:01,080
I got it from the previous game.

142
00:12:01,110 --> 00:12:02,440
Are you done analysing?

143
00:12:02,630 --> 00:12:03,630
Go that way.

144
00:12:04,430 --> 00:12:05,630
How did you know that?

145
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:09,300
There is an arrow.

146
00:12:09,310 --> 00:12:11,230
Are you really gonna follow the arrow?

147
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:13,230
You don't even know who left it here.

148
00:12:13,550 --> 00:12:14,550
It's up to you.

149
00:12:14,870 --> 00:12:15,990
There are many tunnels here.

150
00:12:15,990 --> 00:12:18,590
It must be a public underground
defence facility.

151
00:12:18,590 --> 00:12:20,920
No one would dig all these tunnels for fun.

152
00:12:21,150 --> 00:12:23,280
If you don't want to go, just stay here.

153
00:12:23,870 --> 00:12:24,870
You...

154
00:12:28,070 --> 00:12:29,190
What should we do now?

155
00:12:29,190 --> 00:12:30,650
We can't even find the key.

156
00:12:31,230 --> 00:12:32,390
Forget the key,

157
00:12:32,470 --> 00:12:33,670
how can we get out now?

158
00:12:34,430 --> 00:12:35,430
Let's go.

159
00:12:49,150 --> 00:12:50,590
This seems to be the shelter where

160
00:12:50,590 --> 00:12:52,920
the villagers hid during the wolf plague.

161
00:13:03,790 --> 00:13:05,450
This quilt looks so familiar.

162
00:13:07,390 --> 00:13:08,390
Yeah.

163
00:13:08,430 --> 00:13:10,160
I think I've seen it somewhere.

164
00:13:11,590 --> 00:13:12,590
Look at this.

165
00:13:16,270 --> 00:13:18,000
It looks like a child's doodle.

166
00:13:19,230 --> 00:13:20,830
No kid dares to draw here.

167
00:13:21,750 --> 00:13:23,610
Could it be that thing's drawing?

168
00:13:26,390 --> 00:13:27,520
The one who drew this

169
00:13:28,350 --> 00:13:29,480
must be very lonely.

170
00:13:31,470 --> 00:13:32,670
You're so sensitive.

171
00:13:33,350 --> 00:13:35,440
Hurry, let's get out of this place.

172
00:13:36,350 --> 00:13:37,350
Let's go.

173
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:16,150
This is the fourth time

174
00:14:16,340 --> 00:14:18,140
but I've never seen this before.

175
00:14:18,470 --> 00:14:20,070
The Door Ghost took the key.

176
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:21,960
I don't know what to do now.

177
00:14:22,710 --> 00:14:24,150
Just stay alive.

178
00:14:24,630 --> 00:14:25,950
We still don't know

179
00:14:25,950 --> 00:14:27,680
what the taboo conditions are.

180
00:14:28,110 --> 00:14:30,270
Usually, there's only one taboo condition.

181
00:14:30,270 --> 00:14:31,710
and there are patterns.

182
00:14:32,590 --> 00:14:34,270
This time, we have various conditions.

183
00:14:34,270 --> 00:14:35,800
I can't figure it out at all.

184
00:14:36,590 --> 00:14:38,910
It means there are many taboo conditions.

185
00:14:38,910 --> 00:14:40,430
Even if there are many,

186
00:14:41,430 --> 00:14:43,150
there has to be a pattern.

187
00:14:45,550 --> 00:14:46,550
Sorry, guys.

188
00:14:47,550 --> 00:14:48,910
I lost the key.

189
00:14:49,390 --> 00:14:51,110
I think our top priority now

190
00:14:51,150 --> 00:14:52,470
is to work together

191
00:14:52,510 --> 00:14:53,670
and find a way out.

192
00:14:54,510 --> 00:14:56,170
There are only four of us left.

193
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:59,070
Who knows the conditions? Let's share them.

194
00:14:59,270 --> 00:15:01,510
I don't want to lose any of us again.

195
00:15:03,510 --> 00:15:05,030
Who would share the clues?

196
00:15:05,630 --> 00:15:06,830
Interesting.

197
00:15:07,550 --> 00:15:08,790
You look smart

198
00:15:08,830 --> 00:15:10,150
but you sound silly.

199
00:15:11,510 --> 00:15:13,910
Don't you know that fortune favours fools?

200
00:15:18,830 --> 00:15:20,360
Since we entering the door,

201
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:22,740
the female ghost has taken four actions.

202
00:15:23,710 --> 00:15:25,030
On the first night,

203
00:15:25,390 --> 00:15:27,550
Wu died alone on the rooftop.

204
00:15:28,390 --> 00:15:29,430
The second day,

205
00:15:29,670 --> 00:15:31,670
we went up the mountain to cut trees.

206
00:15:32,070 --> 00:15:33,870
Three of us carried the tree

207
00:15:34,310 --> 00:15:36,310
and were killed by the female ghost.

208
00:15:36,550 --> 00:15:39,070
Zhang Zishuang entered the temple at night

209
00:15:39,310 --> 00:15:41,240
and was killed by the female ghost.

210
00:15:41,670 --> 00:15:43,310
Cheng Wen, Wang Xiaoyi.

211
00:15:45,990 --> 00:15:47,910
Wang Xiaoyi was alone by the well,

212
00:15:48,230 --> 00:15:50,230
but the female ghost didn't show up.

213
00:15:50,510 --> 00:15:51,970
When Cheng Wen went there,

214
00:15:52,590 --> 00:15:54,120
the female ghost appeared.

215
00:15:54,590 --> 00:15:56,870
One, three, one, two.

216
00:15:58,350 --> 00:16:00,750
The clue seems to be related to the numbers.

217
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:03,080
No.

218
00:16:03,470 --> 00:16:04,600
Not only the number,

219
00:16:05,470 --> 00:16:06,470
One, railing.

220
00:16:07,070 --> 00:16:08,070
Three, tree.

221
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:09,510
One, temple.

222
00:16:09,510 --> 00:16:10,510
Two, well.

223
00:16:11,030 --> 00:16:12,350
One person doesn't enter the temple.

224
00:16:12,350 --> 00:16:13,790
Two people don't look at the well.

225
00:16:13,790 --> 00:16:15,650
Three people don't hold the tree.

226
00:16:16,310 --> 00:16:18,510
One person doesn't lean on the railing.

227
00:16:20,430 --> 00:16:21,710
I was right about you.

228
00:16:22,950 --> 00:16:23,950
I am right?

229
00:16:25,830 --> 00:16:27,910
You already knew the clues of this door?

230
00:16:27,910 --> 00:16:29,510
You denied it when I asked you that day.

231
00:16:29,510 --> 00:16:30,870
Do you know how many will die because of it?

232
00:16:30,870 --> 00:16:31,870
Ridiculous.

233
00:16:32,510 --> 00:16:34,310
It's that monster that killed them.

234
00:16:34,310 --> 00:16:35,970
What does it have to do with me?

235
00:16:36,230 --> 00:16:38,150
But you already know the taboo conditions.

236
00:16:38,150 --> 00:16:39,030
Why didn't you say anything?

237
00:16:39,030 --> 00:16:40,030
Say anything?

238
00:16:40,990 --> 00:16:43,250
I hope the person I saved is worth saving.

239
00:16:43,870 --> 00:16:45,190
Think about it.

240
00:16:45,550 --> 00:16:47,750
I warned us before entering the temple.

241
00:16:47,750 --> 00:16:50,030
Listen to me or not, it's up to them.

242
00:16:50,630 --> 00:16:52,030
It's not my job

243
00:16:52,150 --> 00:16:53,540
to make an effort to save them.

244
00:16:53,540 --> 00:16:54,540
Besides,

245
00:16:54,630 --> 00:16:55,830
you are experienced.

246
00:16:56,590 --> 00:16:58,870
Didn't anyone try to hurt you in the door?

247
00:16:59,190 --> 00:17:00,850
And you want me to share clues?

248
00:17:01,070 --> 00:17:01,670
What?

249
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:03,670
If I say I have it two days ago,

250
00:17:03,710 --> 00:17:04,910
would you believe me?

251
00:17:06,510 --> 00:17:07,970
You're questioning me now

252
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:10,589
because you were threatened.

253
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:13,440
When Wang Xiaoyi was in trouble,

254
00:17:13,550 --> 00:17:15,910
I didn't see you guys so riled up.

255
00:17:16,230 --> 00:17:17,230
Enough!

256
00:17:20,829 --> 00:17:22,290
I'll lure the monster out.

257
00:17:22,579 --> 00:17:23,950
- OK. - No.

258
00:17:24,030 --> 00:17:26,030
Since we've got the taboo conditions,

259
00:17:26,030 --> 00:17:27,150
we can't get out

260
00:17:27,550 --> 00:17:28,630
if we avoid them.

261
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:31,310
We'll die either way.

262
00:17:32,950 --> 00:17:34,510
It's better to set a trap

263
00:17:35,190 --> 00:17:37,850
and lure the monster out
with taboo conditions.

264
00:17:38,380 --> 00:17:40,470
Maybe we still have a chance
to get the key back.

265
00:17:40,470 --> 00:17:41,700
No, Xiong.

266
00:17:41,830 --> 00:17:42,870
I disagree.

267
00:17:43,750 --> 00:17:44,750
What?

268
00:17:45,470 --> 00:17:47,870
Do you want to negotiate with that monster?

269
00:17:48,030 --> 00:17:50,090
As long as she lives, we can't get out.

270
00:17:50,870 --> 00:17:52,870
It's better than waiting for death.

271
00:17:54,990 --> 00:17:56,510
She seems to be afraid of fire.

272
00:17:56,510 --> 00:17:58,830
I saved Ruan Baijie with fire before.

273
00:18:28,710 --> 00:18:31,190
Although you can't bless me to go out,

274
00:18:32,270 --> 00:18:34,390
I still hope everything goes well.

275
00:19:13,310 --> 00:19:14,310
Go!

276
00:19:34,230 --> 00:19:35,230
Xiong.

277
00:19:48,030 --> 00:19:49,030
Run!

278
00:19:58,550 --> 00:19:59,670
Come at me!

279
00:20:15,150 --> 00:20:16,750
I've seen your painting.

280
00:20:17,110 --> 00:20:18,000
You...

281
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:18,870
I...

282
00:20:18,870 --> 00:20:19,990
I've seen your...

283
00:20:20,470 --> 00:20:21,470
your painting.

284
00:20:23,830 --> 00:20:26,070
You must be very lonely too.

285
00:21:00,550 --> 00:21:02,350
You fought so fiercely just now.

286
00:21:02,350 --> 00:21:03,350
How's your wound?

287
00:21:03,950 --> 00:21:04,950
